      <issueAreaCode>EDU</issueAreaCode>
      <specific_issues>
        <description>Protection of home education from government regulation - meetings with Members of Congress and their staff to talk about general homeschooling success and to ask Congress to "leave us alone."

HSLDA strongly opposes more federal involvement in early education, and continues to meet with Members of Congress and their staff to oppose any expansion in this area in upcoming legislation generally.

HSLDA opposed the confirmation of John King to the be U.S. Secretary of Education. We met with Senate Members and Staff urging his rejection due to his support for the Common Core State Standards Initiative, and sent out nationwide action alerts urging citizens to call their U.S. Senators and urge that John King be rejected.</description>
      </specific_issues>
