      <issueAreaCode>FAM</issueAreaCode>
      <specific_issues>
        <description>Speaking with staff and Members about the dangers of the U.N. Convention on the Rights of the Child.

Speaking with staff and Members about the dangers of the U.N. Convention On the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination Against Women.

Speaking with staff and Members about the dangers of the U.N. Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities.

All these treaties threaten parental rights, homeschool freedom, and US sovereignty.

Meetings with Members of House and Senate and their staff to urge them to support the Parental Rights Amendment. It was introduced in the 113th Congress in the House as H.J.Res. 50, and in the Senate as S.J.Res. 37. The Amendment would preserve the right of parents to direct the education, upbringing, and care of their children. </description>
      </specific_issues>
